cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a system that aids job seekers in acquiring social skills for job interviews. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper describes a software pipeline that uses computational methods to generate affective reactions in a virtual recruiter. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper mentions a recognition module that detects user behaviours, which could involve natural language processing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is possible as the system may use visual cues to detect user behaviours. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the system may use machine learning algorithms to improve its performance over time.
